val SD = sqlContext.sql("select * from accesslog where type like \"%ServiceDispatcherServlet%\"")
SD.registerTempTable("sd")

val SD200 = SD.filter(SD("status")===200)
SD200.registerTempTable("sd200")

/**
 * Get Http Status Code Information
 **/
case class http(desc: String, Type: String)
val httpCode = Map(
    200->http("OK","Success"),
    400-> http("Bad Request","Client Error"),
    500-> http("Internal Server Error","Server Error"))
    
def getCodeDesc(code : Int) = {
    if(httpCode.contains(code)) httpCode(code).desc
    else "null"
}
def getCodeType(code : Int) = {
    if(httpCode.contains(code)) httpCode(code).Type
    else "null"
}
sqlc.udf.register("CodeDesc", getCodeDesc _)
sqlc.udf.register("CodeType", getCodeType _)

/**
 * caculating percentile of processTime
**/
import spark.implicits._
import com.tdunning.math.stats.TDigest
import org.apache.spark.sql.catalyst.encoders.RowEncoder
import org.apache.spark.sql.types._
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row

//ss200: dataframe of which its status = 200
//processTime: data of column of processTime
val ss200 = sqlContext.sql("select * from sd where status = 200")
val processTime = ss200.select("processTime").map(r=>r(0).asInstanceOf[Long]).collect()
val td = TDigest.createDigest(100d)
processTime.map(r=>td.add(r))

//0.5  0.9  0.99  0.999
println("50 percentile of processTime : " + td.quantile(0.5)+'\n')
println("90 percentile of processTime : " + td.quantile(0.9)+'\n')
println("99 percentile of processTime : " + td.quantile(0.99)+'\n')
println("99.9 percentile of processTime : " + td.quantile(0.999)+'\n')

//anomalies of processTime of ServiceDispatcherServlet
sqlContext.sql("select * from sd where status = 200 and processTime > 1.279783358774663E7").registerTempTable("anoPro")

val anoSort = sqlContext.sql("select sortByHour, count(1) as sum from anoPro group by sortByHour order by sortByHour")
val anoSortList = anoSort.map(r=>(r(0).asInstanceOf[String].substring(0,10),r(0).asInstanceOf[String].substring(11,13).toInt,r(1).asInstanceOf[Long])).collect()
